[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"413824\">@Gary Guo</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"531558\">@Wedson Almeida Filho</span> , details are in the following link:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/Y8s1evi1wY1XlVgG@boqun-archlinux/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/Y8s1evi1wY1XlVgG@boqun-archlinux/</a></p>\n<p>I think we can implement <code>ArcBorrow</code> as</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Clone, Copy)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 322644625,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674262118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/Isn't.20.60ArcBorrow.60.20just.20.60.26ArcInner.3CT.3E.60.3F/near/322644625\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"531558\">Wedson Almeida Filho</span> , details are in the following link:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/Y8s1evi1wY1XlVgG@boqun-archlinux/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/Y8s1evi1wY1XlVgG@boqun-archlinux/</a></p>\n<p>I think we can implement <code>ArcBorrow</code> as</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Clone, Copy)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Oh, I haven't looked at the details yet but if this works, I really like this simplification.</p>\n<p>I actually think we should rename <code>ArcInner</code> to something else (suggestions?) and just use <code>&amp;Whatever&lt;T&gt;</code> because this syntax is more common and less cryptic than <code>Whatever&lt;'_, T&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 322647235,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1674263735
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Ref&lt;T&gt;</code>? <span aria-label=\"joy\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f602\" role=\"img\" title=\"joy\">:joy:</span></p>",
        "id": 322647679,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674264036
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We still couldn't use derive due to bound issues</p>",
        "id": 322656710,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1674271159
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, you're right, but if we can do <code>&amp;Whatever&lt;T&gt;</code>, we get <code>Copy</code> and <code>Clone</code> automatically</p>",
        "id": 322663141,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674276369
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/Isn't.20.60ArcBorrow.60.20just.20.60.26ArcInner.3CT.3E.60.3F/near/322656710\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We still couldn't use derive due to bound issues</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Found a workaround</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\">// need to public `ArcInner` first</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">ArcInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">// Introduce an external layer, may have users in other place as well</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Copy, Clone)]</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Ptr</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">P</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Deref</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">put</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Ptr</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>We need <code>Ptr</code> since we want to:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Deref</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>, otherwise we can just use tuple type:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">put</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcInner</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 322799791,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674352412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>IMO I'd prefer <code>Ptr</code>, more easier to understand in compilation error messages than a tuple.</p>",
        "id": 322810026,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Rodriguez Reboredo",
        "timestamp": 1674362748
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We don't need a different type, we can just use <code>&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;</code>. We should rename it though.</p>",
        "id": 322811400,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1674363876
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"531558\">Wedson Almeida Filho</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/Isn't.20.60ArcBorrow.60.20just.20.60.26ArcInner.3CT.3E.60.3F/near/322811400\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We don't need a different type, we can just use <code>&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;</code>. We should rename it though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>But we want to use <code>&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;</code> as <code>Deref&lt;Target=T&gt;</code>, right? And I haven't found a way to support that ;-(</p>",
        "id": 322815552,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674367826
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We just need to implement <code>Deref</code>.</p>\n<p>Here's the whole change in <code>rust</code>, just need to cleanup documentation:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/wedsonaf/linux/commit/a052f2194268a96cd99ce309bc68345780907f1c\">https://github.com/wedsonaf/linux/commit/a052f2194268a96cd99ce309bc68345780907f1c</a></p>",
        "id": 322815672,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1674367961
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, you make <code>ArcInner&lt;T&gt;: Deref&lt;Target=T&gt;</code>, looks like it works ;-)</p>",
        "id": 322815836,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674368143
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I was thinking we need <code>&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;: Deref&lt;Target=T&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 322815909,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1674368177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note the signature of <code>deref</code>: <code>fn deref(&amp;self) -&gt; &amp;Self::Target</code>. If you implement <code>Deref</code> for <code>&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;</code>, the <code>self</code> type would be <code>&amp;&amp;ArcInner&lt;T&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 322815972,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1674368269
    },
    {
