    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"641029\">baul</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/Isn't.20.60ArcBorrow.60.20just.20.60.26ArcInner.3CT.3E.60.3F/near/392233104\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"531558\">Wedson Almeida Filho</span>  before the pr, we still use the GAT.  So which one feature of GAT  lead you to just use the &amp;Arcinner&lt;T&gt;, and remove the ArcBorrow. I dont get it, can you explain this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Please read this zulip thread, the PR was mentioned here for a reason ;-)</p>",
