    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"641029\">@baul</span> I wrote <code>ArcBorrow</code> (then called <code>RefBorrow</code>) before the GAT feature was even complete. So the <code>ForeignOwnable::Borrowed</code> (then called <code>PointerWrapper::Borrowed</code>) associated type couldn't have a lifetime associated with it. So we had <code>ArcBorrow</code> for <code>Arc</code> (then called <code>Ref</code>) and <code>UnsafeReference</code> for <code>Box</code>.</p>\n<p>When GATs were completed (and even before they were stabilised), we started using them. The commit below is available in the <code>rust</code> branch:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">commit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40839</span><span class=\"n\">c04dcd2d772367de3cac1e987271e78b5b6</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Author</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Wedson</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Almeida</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Filho</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">wedsonaf</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">com</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Date</span>:   <span class=\"nc\">Fri</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nov</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">12</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">21</span>:<span class=\"mi\">22</span>:<span class=\"mi\">09</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2021</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"mi\">0000</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span>: <span class=\"nc\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">generic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">associated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">types</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">GATs</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implement</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">PointerWrapper</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">The</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">feature</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">although</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">still</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unstable</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">no</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">longer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">incomplete</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">It</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">allows</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">us</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">lifetime</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">Borrow</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">assocciated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">which</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">allows</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">us</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simplify</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">code</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">around</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">borrowing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wrapped</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">also</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allows</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">us</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">wrap</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">raw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pointers</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">integers</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">without</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">violating</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">Deref</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">recommendations</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Signed</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">off</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">by</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Wedson</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Almeida</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Filho</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">wedsonaf</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">google</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">com</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>At the time I removed <code>UnsafeReference&lt;T&gt;</code> in favour of <code>&amp;T</code> but I didn't realise that I could do something similar for <code>ArcBorrow</code>. Thankfully <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411647\">@Boqun Feng</span> realised this a few months back.</p>\n<p>Well, better late than never! Here we are :)</p>\n<p>Does it make sense to you now?</p>",
        "id": 392333295,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1695306466
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks you.  It is helpful for me to review/read some list before.<br>\nTo use GAT, in  ForeignOwnable' define, the associated type must have a explict lifetime. Before the patch, you impl a gat type by </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">Borrowed</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>now use </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">Borrowed</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithRef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>as you said <code>I actually think we should rename ArcInner to something else (suggestions?) and just use &amp;Whatever&lt;T&gt; because this syntax is more common and less cryptic than Whatever&lt;'_, T&gt;</code>.</p>\n<p>From another viewport, to create a  Borrowed&lt;'a&gt; which a type have lifetime generic, we have two way:  &amp;A1 or A2&lt;a'&gt;.  The new pr use the &amp;A1 way.</p>\n<p>Thank you all.</p>",
        "id": 392440926,
        "sender_full_name": "Baul (Jianguo Bao)",
        "timestamp": 1695359439
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>review here, find network disconnect period, cannot use mutt.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// This is useful when the argument of a function call is an [`ArcBorrow`] (e.g., in a method</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// receiver), but we have an [`Arc`] instead. Getting an [`ArcBorrow`] is free when optimised.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// This is useful when the argument of a function call is a [`WithRef`] (e.g., in a method</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// receiver), but we have an [`Arc`] instead. Getting a [`WithRef`] is free when optimised.</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">/// This is useful when the argument of a function call is a [`&amp;WithRef`] (e.g., in a method</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sd\">/// receiver), but we have an [`Arc`] instead. Getting a [`&amp;WithRef`] is free when optimised.</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Look</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">like</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">vs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">WithRef</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">vs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithRef</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">So</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">need</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">stat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">difference</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"cp\">#[inline]</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">as_arc_borrow</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">ArcBorrow</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"nb\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">as_with_ref</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">WithRef</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">proper</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n<span class=\"n\">If</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">follow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as_arc_borrow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">naming</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as_with_ref</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">should</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithRef</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">WithRef</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"n\">If</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">follow</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">convention</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">std</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">should</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">as_withref_ref</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n<span class=\"n\">If</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">just</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">express</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">borrowed</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arc</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">even</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">have</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">optimized</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">arc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">Withref</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">can</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">also</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">the</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">name</span>\n<span class=\"n\">as_arc_borrow</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">?</span>\n\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"c1\">// SAFETY: The constraint that the lifetime of the shared reference must outlive that of</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// the returned `ArcBorrow` ensures that the object remains alive and that no mutable</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// the returned `WithRef` ensures that the object remains alive and that no mutable</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"c1\">// reference can be created.</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ArcBorrow</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ptr</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">as_ref</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"sd\">/// However, when one may need to increment the refcount, it is preferable to use an `ArcBorrow&lt;T&gt;`</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"sd\">/// over `&amp;Arc&lt;T&gt;` because the latter results in a double-indirection: a pointer (shared reference)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"sd\">/// to a pointer (`Arc&lt;T&gt;`) to the object (`T`). An [`ArcBorrow`] eliminates this double</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"sd\">/// indirection while still allowing one to increment the refcount and getting an `Arc&lt;T&gt;` when/if</span>\n<span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"sd\">/// needed.</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">This</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">stmt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">should</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">be</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kept</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">as_with_ref</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">so</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">we</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">can</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">understanding</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">why</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">introduce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">and</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">why</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">public</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 392840713,
        "sender_full_name": "Baul (Jianguo Bao)",
        "timestamp": 1695567353
    },
